Risks, partnerships, and source links
Risk analysis and mitigation
Numerical instability risk (NeuroPulse)
Multi-compartment coupling increases stiffness; incorrect dt settings can generate misleading behavior.
Mitigation: stability checks, adaptive dt suggestions, validation harness vs reference outputs. 

Scientific misinterpretation / “medical device” framing risk
The project explicitly states it is not a medical device.
Mitigation: stronger disclaimers, export watermarking, safe phrasing, remove/rename any features that appear prescriptive, and document intended use cases.

Security risk (browser exports, clipboard, file handling)
Browser APIs vary by context (file:// vs localhost).
Mitigation: default to local server workflows; document permissions; avoid unsafe external loads.

Maintainability risk (monolithic files)
Large, intertwined single-file apps become brittle.
Mitigation: modular extraction + plugin boundaries + coding standards.

ML evaluation risk (Combined-Agents)
Without standardized benchmarks, improvements can appear due to noise/non-determinism.
Mitigation: deterministic runs, repeated trials, confidence intervals, standardized tasks/metrics. 

